summary: Blimey 3 consecutive nights of Marvel dreams. Night #1 We're all fighting Thanos but i balls it up by jumping the gun and...
body: Blimey 3 consecutive nights of Marvel dreams. Night #1 We’re all fighting Thanos but i balls it up by jumping the gun and attacking him too soon. Night #2 Cap and Starlord are at a really rubbish pool party. Someone’s eating gravity resistant popcorn, Nick Fury’s hogging the TV remote and Cap’s stressed cos he’s late for a job interview. Night #3 Spiderman’s pulling the One Ring from the bottom of a lake. Then he takes his shirt off cos of course he does. Feel free to use any of this, Marvel.

body:
I give up

I’ve been trying to find a good Doctor Who crossover for days, because crossovers are awesome, right?

And I thought “The Doctor would probably slap the shit out of Thanos, so why not an Avenger crossover??”

GUYS. They’re ALL SuperWhoAvengeLock. Even the ones not marked as such. EVERY. GODDAMN. ONE.

I just want to see a tiny blonde woman put the fear of god in an oversized rotten grape is that too much to ask

title: And You Were Mine
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2FING5e

by ThatEreriGirl

Tony has been stuck inside a tower with his five other siblings for his whole entire 17 years of being alive. And every time his birthday passes, those lights, that look so beautiful and so magical, light up the night sky. It’s always on his birthday, without fail, and he can’t help but feel like they’re made just for him. All he wants for his 18th birthday is to see them in real life, and not from some far away tower. But Fury, as every other time, absolutely forbids it. Tony feels hopeless, but what will happen when a random stranger with piercing green eyes suddenly pops up at his tower, with a mission in mind?
Or
A Frostiron version of the Disney movie Tangled (my favorite Disney movie of all damn times).
*Currently looking for a beta with a lot of writing experience! (Not just fanfic, but other works as well, off of this site)

Tony has been stuck inside a tower with his five other siblings for his whole entire 17 years of being alive. And every time his birthday passes, those lights, that look so beautiful and so magical, light up the night sky. It’s always on his birthday, without fail, and he can’t help but feel like they’re made just for him. All he wants for his 18th birthday is to see them in real life, and not from some far away tower. But Fury, as every other time, absolutely forbids it. Tony feels hopeless, but what will happen when a random stranger with piercing green eyes suddenly pops up at his tower, with a mission in mind?

A Frostiron version of the Disney movie Tangled (my favorite Disney movie of all damn times).

body:
Angry Peter

I cannot stress to you guys enough how much I love sweet/patient characters snapping. Like you get so used to them being this literal cinnamon roll and then they flip the switch for a second. Let’s take one of my favorite characters.

Peter Parker

Peter Parker has a natural type a personality. He’s super sweet and he’s hardworking and he’s a self-sacrificing idiot who we all know and love. We’ve seen him get sad, happy, guilty, upset and frustrated but we haven’t really seen him snap. We haven’t seen that inner beast we all know is in there. I would picture it like this.

Peter’s at the end of his rope. It had basically been an all around terrible month, cuz we all know out baby boi isn’t about to snap after one day. But it’s been tough lately. But all Peter can feel is just pure rage. He wants to go on a rampage but he keeps bottling up.

It’s about time he explodes.

It just starts as a nagging feeling in the back of his skull that he almost mistakes for his spidey sense.

Hes just chilling on the couch in the Avengers common room after a tiny mission in Manhattan. He was trying reign in his emotions that seem to not go away like he wants them to.

The Avengers had a little bit of a hard time accepting that Spidey is a literal teenager. And sometimes it shows in their actions, their incessant need to shelter him from any problem that arises. They often found that he was independent, he wasn’t part of the Avengers so he didn’t exactly heed orders. If he found them reasonable he listened, but if they were ‘fall back’ because they didn’t see him fit, you bet your ass he didn’t listen.

But they didn’t treat him like he was dumb when they only knew him as Spider-Man. Now to them he was Peter Parker, and Peter Parker only.

He actually ended up catching the guy himself. Though he was a little disappointed that everyone else waved him off before he could tell them of his plan. It kinda left most things up to him and it was difficult as hell trying to cover everywhere he had originally planned the Avengers being.

Peter had had an actual plan and it worked! He was feeling a little better because he caught a bad guy. That was the one thing he could truly rely on to make him feel better. Putting another criminal away to keep the streets a little more safe.

The others were a little miffed at him because he went off on his own and he was a literal child and they had actually taken a bit of a liking to him. Momma Steve was the most mad so he confronted Peter, who looked proud of himself.

Then he goes off. “What the hell were you thinking?!” He continues to scold Peter about his reckless behavior and some of the Avengers also chime in as well to lecture the vigilante.

“You didn’t even have a plan! It was idiotic and showed your incompetence! You are a literal teenager!” That was what pushed Peter past his breaking point. He exhaled sharply and a glare found a way onto his face before he could stop it.

“Shut up.”

It was a shock to everyone really. Peter was practically an angel to them, he sassed them but he wasn’t downright rude. When they caught a glimpse of his pissed off expression they felt their blood freeze. Even Natasha got a bit of goosebumps.

Peter’s voice was cold and filled to the brim with a venom that left everyone in the room paralyzed. “You should really stop using the words 'idiot’ and 'incompetent’ as if they mean the same thing as 'teenager’. I had a plan, but you all waved me off at the beginning and left me to do it myself. And if you haven’t noticed, I put away the guy before any if you could even lay a hand on him. Is that incompetent to you? If it is, you better reevaluate yourself.”

He then went into extreme detail of his plan. It had been extremely thought out with almost zero way of it ending without the guy behind bars. They had even played a role in it, he had made sure to include them within the plan and trust them enough to do it. They had failed and left him to clean up the mess.

Frankly, Peter was terrifying. The look screamed cold-blooded fury. He didn’t explode in a rage like most people would. He didn’t scream and yell. He didn’t look fiery.

His heart froze over and words clicked into the right place and he said them with the tone that left them unable to breathe right. A tone that was strong and so unbelievably cold and he wasn’t even yelling.

The atmosphere was suffocating.

Peter walked calmly out of the room, but not without tense shoulders. Tony was the first one to snap out of it. That didn’t seem like the Peter Parker or Spider-Man to him.

That seemed like someone completely new.
